{"title":"Devinci’s New E-Troy Lite Includes Bosch SX Motor for Light-Weight eMTB Performance & MTB Handling","link":"https://bikerumor.com/devinci-e-troy-lite-emtb-bosch-sx/","date":1713967813000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Yoann-Barelli-slash-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Yoann Barelli, slash\" /></p>\n<p>Canada’s Devinci Cycles has officially entered the ‘light eMTB’ category with their new E-Troy Lite. This all-new model is built around Devinci’s versatile Troy trail bike and features an aluminum frame, 150/160mm travel, and a mixed wheelset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The E-Troy Lite’s Bosch Performance Line SX motor provides ample power to help you up the climbs but in a light enough package to go nearly unnoticed while you’re descending. Devinci built this bike for those who want a little assistance or extra range, but still want to ride a bike that feels natural and agile when you’re rallying downhill.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Devinci E-Troy Lite – Frame Details:</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, intro image\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-intro-image-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Touting its durability, stiffness, and an excellent strength-to-weight ratio, Devinci stuck with a 6061-T6 aluminum frame for the E-Troy Lite. The frame offers 150mm rear travel, and all models come with 160mm forks. The E-Troy Lite is built around an MX wheelset.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, linkage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-linkage-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Devinci has specifically optimized the E-Troy Lite’s Split Pivot suspension linkage for eMTBs. The tune aims to keep the suspension highly active even while accelerating, ensuring great traction and maximizing the motor’s torque. Furthermore, the linkage is also tuned to compensate for the added weight of the bike’s motor, and its mixed wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Split Pivot linkage is designed to separate acceleration and braking forces, and offer highly sensitive small-bump compliance. To keep that suspension running smoothly for the long haul, the E-Troy Lite’s frame is built with Enduro double-lip bearings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, motor shield\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-motor-shield-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Devinci has devised a nylon motor shield for the E-Troy Lite, which is vented to help heat and water escape. The frame also gets a chainstay protector.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An upper chain guide is included on these bikes, and all frame sizes have room for a 500ml water bottle (or larger), even with a piggyback shock. Devinci provides one water bottle mount on top of the down tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Fitments:</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, rear axle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-rear-axle-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As for fitments, the E-Troy Lite frames use Boost 148mm rear axle spacing and run a 55mm chainline. The frame has clearance for up to 2.6” wide tires, and Devinci has adopted SRAM’s UDH derailleur hanger.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, cable routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-cable-routing-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frames feature internal cable routing, with a slick design up front. The cables/hoses go straight into the frame’s small entry ports at the head tube to prevent rattling or rubbing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, dropper post\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-seat-post-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>E-Troy Lite frames accept 31.6mm seat posts, and max insertion lengths by size are as follows: S – 240mm, M – 270mm, L – 300, XL – 340mm. Small frames come stock with 150mm posts, mediums get 175mm, and large and XL bikes run 200mm posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Drive System:</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Bosch Performance Line SX motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-Performance-Line-SX-motor-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To power the E-Troy Lite, Devinci went with Bosch’s newest and lightest motor, the Performance Line SX. The motor produces 55Nm of torque and a maximum output of 600 Watts. Devinci has neatly integrated the system’s speed sensor into the dropout.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Bosch CompactTube 400 battery\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-CompactTube-400-battery-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Inside the frame’s down tube is a 400Wh Bosch CompactTube 400 battery, which was purpose-built with rugged construction for eMTB applications. The in-frame charge port is located on top of the down tube just above the BB.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bosch’s 4A charger fully charges the battery in 3.5 hours, and brings it to 50% in 1.5 hours. A full charge should assist for around two hours of riding, roughly 3280ft of climbing, and an average distance of 25 miles. In Turbo mode, the range reduces to about 17 miles. In eco mode and under ideal conditions, the bike can provide up to 42 miles of assist.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This drive system is also compatible with Bosch’s Powermore 250 range extender battery, which mounts to a water bottle mount and adds another 250Wh of capacity. The battery is about the same size as a water bottle, and plugs into the frame charge port.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Bosch top tube display\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-top-tube-display-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The E-Tory Lite’s frame includes Bosch’s top-tube mounted display unit. The unit includes the power button, and shows your assist level and battery life. It can also be used to toggle between assist levels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Bosch mini remote\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Bosch-mini-remote-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While riding, Bosch’s wireless mini remote handlebar controller provides ergonomic, thumb-activated controls that are easy to use without moving your hand position.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This drive system connects to Bosch’s eBike Flow App. The app features include customization of drive system settings, ride metric tracking, software updates, and synchronization with Strava.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Geometry:</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"606\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite geometry chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart-297x150.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart-120x61.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-geometry-chart-768x388.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As the above chart shows, E-Troy Lite frames are available in small, medium, large and XL sizes. Devinci gave the E-Troy Lite a slack head tube angle of 63.6°, and the steep seat mast angles range slightly from 77.9° to 77.5° depending on frame size.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reach numbers remain pretty conservative at 461mm for a size medium, or 481mm for a large. Chainstay length for all frame sizes is 438mm. BB height is 346mm, and Devinci has kept stack heights fairly low across the board. See the chart above for all other figures.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Model Lineup:</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The E-Troy Lite will be available in three different build options.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>GX AXS 12s – $7399</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite GX AXS 12s, side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-side-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The GX AXS 12s is available in a Gloss/AL13 frame color.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs.jpg\"><img width=\"1221\" height=\"643\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite GX AXS 12s specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs.jpg 1221w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs-297x156.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs-120x63.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-AXS-12s-specs-768x404.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>GX 12s – $6399</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite GX 12s, side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-side-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The GX 12s model also comes in the Gloss/AL13 color.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs.jpg\"><img width=\"1219\" height=\"631\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite GX 12s specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs.jpg 1219w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs-297x154.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs-120x62.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-GX-12s-specs-768x398.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>NX 12s – $5499</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite NX 12s, side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-side-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The NX 12s model gets a Gloss/Digital Lavender paint job.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs.jpg\"><img width=\"1223\" height=\"623\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite NX 12s specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs.jpg 1223w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs-297x151.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs-120x61.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-NX-12s-specs-768x391.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Yoann-Barelli-air.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Yoann-Barelli-air.jpg\" alt=\"Devinci E-Troy Lite, Yoann Barelli, air\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Devinci-E-Troy-Lite-Yoann-Barelli-air.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-conte